<br />
Person B&#39;s debt would be assigned a value, probably under a mark to market accounting system.  That value would then be applied to whoever was owed money by Person A.<br />
<br />
So it works like this;<br />
<br />
I borrow money from Enrique to set up a business. I buy a bunch of Sirius XM bonds.  I declare bankruptcy (but Sirius XM is still in business)<br />
<br />
The bankruptcy judge determines a value for those bonds, probably based on market value.  They are then sold to pay back whatever can be paid back to Enrique.<br />
