- Enrique <br><BR><font size=1>12:53 11-01-2011</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a></B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/magic/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=<a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a>'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">Pat Sullivan and I don&#39;t always agree on everything. While we like each other, on topics ranging from president Obama to Xbox 360, we disagree.  However, one thing he, I and about everyone else agreed upon was this; The most important thing the government needed to do to prevent another meltdown was regulate LEVERAGE in institutions.<br />
<br />
What&#39;s leverage? Borrowed money.  A company borrows against its assets to buy more assets. Think of someone mortgaging a house to buy another house, then mortgaging that house to buy another.  That&#39;s leverage.  It juices your gains, but when things turn against you, your goose is cooked. It&#39;s what destroyed Bear Stearns and Lehman Bros.<br />
<br />
At the height of the financial crisis, some companies where taking out $40 for every $1 they had and betting it on things like Mortgages or Oil.  When their portfolios dropped even a fraction, their losses were huge; loans were called in; and they were done.<br />
<br />
This was, in my and many other people&#39;s opinions, the single biggest cause of the financial crisis, and yet, noticeably missing in the Dodd Frank bill and Durbin amendment and Volker Rule and every other bill was anything regulating leverage.<br />
<br />
And, 2011 roles around, and we see it again.  MF Global the hedge fund run by Obama-bud Jon Corzine, former governor of New Jersey.  Turns out that not only was he stupid enough to buy Italian and Spanish debt, nooooo, that wasn&#39;t enough. He had to borrow money and bet that too, using again a heart stopping leverage of 40 to 1 to do so.  Needless to say, his company filed for bankruptcy yesterday.<br />
<br />
It&#39;s amazing that this "landmark and historic" piece of legislation didn&#39;t fix the biggest problem: It&#39;s the leverage, stupid. <br><BR><font size=1>12:45 11-01-2011</font><BR><BR>I support the right of our troops to bear arms</TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Iceman </B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/magic/resources/buzz.php?ignorename=Iceman '>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">frist <br><BR><font size=1>12:38 11-01-2011</font></TD></TR><TR><TD colspan='2'><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/magic/resources/buzz.php'>Back to Topics List</A></font></TD></TD></TABLE><P><B>Showing last 30 posts! </b><form action='/magic/resources/buzz.php'><input type='hidden' name='showmore' value='1'><input type='hidden' name='id' value=10001><input type='Submit'  value=' Show all Posts '></form><form action='/magic/resources/buzz.php'><input type='hidden' name='showmore' value='2'><input type='hidden' name='id' value=10001><input type='Submit'  value=' Show Next 30 Posts '></form><p><font class="bfont"><b>You must be a member to add topics to this list.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magic/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font><BR></td></tr></table><script language='javascript'>function quoteboard(quotetext){document.buzzboardform.comments.value = '<i>'+quotetext+'</i><p>';}</script>
